body:
I tested this in full dev and found a small bug where the index.writer.name wasn't being passed to the REST app on startup.  The latest commit fixes that. 

I was able to verify the 2 cases @cestella mentioned.  For the first test I update the bro sensor config:
```
{
  "hdfs": {
    "index": "bro",
    "batchSize": 5,
    "enabled": true
  },
  "elasticsearch": {
    "index": "bro",
    "batchSize": 5,
    "enabled": true
  },
  "solr": {
    "index": "bro_2",
    "batchSize": 5,
    "enabled": true
  }
}
```
A search result now looks like:
```
{
  "id": "44fc8391-474d-4b8e-a375-52f748735b2f",
  "source": {
    ...
    "source.type": "bro"
  },
  "score": 0,
  "index": "bro_2"
}
```
For the next test I deleted the snort indexing config.  A search result against that collection now looks like:
```
{
  "id": "71a0ca1a-b3c2-414b-9fde-c31e8dd5544a",
  "source": {
    ...
    "source.type": "snort"
  },
  "score": 0,
  "index": "snort"
}
```

@ottobackwards I think the main thing there would be to do something like this instead of the rm:

https://github.com/apache/metron/blob/master/dev-utilities/committer-utils/prepare-commit#L100-L107

I wouldn't really want to do a whole lot more refactoring in this PR, just because it's a pretty minor change.
